Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. and  Wendel (MF)  plan to sell 40 million shares in  Legrand SA (LR) , equivalent
to a 15 percent stake in the company, they said in an e-mailed
statement today.  KKR will sell 18.2 million shares and Wendel will offer
21.8 million shares through an accelerated book building to
institutional investors, according to the statement.  Following the sale, the two companies will hold 21.3
percent of Legrandâ€™s capital and 34.1 percent of its voting
